						<handDesc>
							<summary/>
							<handNote>
								<p>Naskh; copied in black ink, with headings and overlinings in red.
								</p>
							</handNote>
						</handDesc>
						<decoDesc>
							<decoNote>Folio 96r contains a table showing different sects’ views on
								determinism and free will. Rulings and headings in red. </decoNote>
						</decoDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>Heavily annotated in the margins. As the author explains (f. 105r),
								he has written notes in the margin himself as well, although it is
								not accepted for the authors to annotate their own work. This
								suggests that the author might have copied the work himself. </p>
							<p>The whole of f. 1r is covered with a note and added verses. </p>
							<p>F. 107 is covered on both sides with notes, one of them by the
								author. </p>
						</additions>
